  "question": "A fair die is rolled twice. A success is when the face that comes up shows 3 or 6. (a) Write the function defining the distribution. (b) Construct a table for the distribution. (c) Construct a histogram for the distribution. (d) Find the mean and the standard deviation for the distribution.",
  "answer": "(a) $p(x) = \\binom{2}{x}\\left(\\frac{1}{3}\\right)^x\\left(\\frac{2}{3}\\right)^{2-x}$. (b) $p(0) = \\binom{2}{0}\\left(\\frac{1}{3}\\right)^0\\left(\\frac{2}{3}\\right)^{2-0} = 0.44$ $p(1) = \\binom{2}{1}\\left(\\frac{1}{3}\\right)^1\\left(\\frac{2}{3}\\right)^{2-1} = 0.44$ $p(2) = \\binom{2}{2}\\left(\\frac{1}{3}\\right)^2\\left(\\frac{2}{3}\\right)^{2-2} = 0.11$. (c) (d) $E(X) = 0.667$ and $\\sigma_X = 0.667$.",
  "explanation": "Answer: (a) $p(x) = \\binom{2}{x}\\left(\\frac{1}{3}\\right)^x\\left(\\frac{2}{3}\\right)^{2-x}$. (b) $p(0) = \\binom{2}{0}\\left(\\frac{1}{3}\\right)^0\\left(\\frac{2}{3}\\right)^{2-0} = 0.44$ $p(1) = \\binom{2}{1}\\left(\\frac{1}{3}\\right)^1\\left(\\frac{2}{3}\\right)^{2-1} = 0.44$ $p(2) = \\binom{2}{2}\\left(\\frac{1}{3}\\right)^2\\left(\\frac{2}{3}\\right)^{2-2} = 0.11$. (c) (d) $E(X) = 0.667$ and $\\sigma_X = 0.667$.",
